Film4.uk.title: Saraband for Dead Lovers
Film4.uk.description: (1948) Historical drama starring Joan Greenwood and Stewart Granger. Princess Dorothea marries the future king of England. But then she meets a Swedish count...

Film4.uk.title: Against the Wind
Film4.uk.description: (1948) Spy thriller. Robert Beatty, Simone Signoret, Jack Warner and Gordon Jackson star as British-trained saboteurs sent to Second World War Belgium. But one of them is a traitor...

Film4.uk.title: Father Brown
Film4.uk.description: (1954) Crime-comedy starring Alec Guinness. A priest is tasked with accompanying a priceless religious artifact from London to Rome. But the prolific thief Flambeau is hot on his trail...

Film4.uk.title: Tolkien
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Biographical drama starring Nicholas Hoult and Lily Collins, charting the early life and inspirations of Lord of the Rings and The Hobbit author JRR Tolkien.

Film4.uk.title: Men in Black: International
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Fourth instalment of the sci-fi comedy franchise with Chris Hemsworth, Tessa Thompson and Liam Neeson. An alien-obsessed rookie joins London's Men in Black team.

Film4.uk.title: Vesper
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Sci-fi fantasy with new-comer Raffiella Chapman and Eddie Marsan. A resourceful teenager scavenges to survive in a mushy and mushroom-y post-apocalyptic world of have and have-nots.

Film4.uk.title: 3:10 to Yuma
Film4.uk.description: (2007) Western starring Christian Bale and Russell Crowe. An impoverished rancher tries to earn some money and his family's respect by escorting a dangerous outlaw on his way to jail.

Film4.uk.title: Amanda
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Mikhael Hers's quietly sensitive drama. A young man becomes responsible for raising his seven-year-old niece after his sister is killed in a Paris terrorist attack. In French/subs.

Film4.uk.title: Time Lock
Film4.uk.description: (1957) Gripping drama with Robert Beatty. An expert team races against the clock to save a six-year-old boy who's been trapped in a seemingly impregnable bank vault.

Film4.uk.title: Patton
Film4.uk.description: (1970) Multi-Oscar-winning, fact-based, Second World War drama starring George C Scott, who gives a vivid portrait of the famously straight-talking US commander General George Patton.

Film4.uk.title: Instant Family
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Comedy. Mark Wahlberg and Rose Byrne star as a couple whose orderly lives are disrupted when they foster three kids. Based on director Sean Anders' own experience.

Film4.uk.title: The Artifice Girl
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Franklin Ritch's strikingly claustrophobic AI thriller. A man creates a virtual nine-year-old to lure online predators from the shadows. But as she learns, she becomes more real...

Film4.uk.title: Alita: Battle Angel
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Partially animated action film based on a popular manga comic. Alita, a deadly cyborg brought back to life by a mourning scientist, sets out to discover her true identity.

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Marple to Huddersfield: Robbie Cumming continues across the Pennines from Marple to Huddersfield, where his journey is hampered by a fallen tree and a leaking lock pound. S1 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Shopping from Home.

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great British Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Witham to Felixstowe: Michael Portillo's railway journey from Canterbury to Skegness reaches Witham in Essex. He visits the factory of the world's oldest supplier of metal-framed windows. S11 Ep13

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great British Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Saxmundham to Norwich: Michael Portillo's journey takes him to the Snape Maltings music and arts venue, the Norfolk seaside resort of Great Yarmouth and the city of Norwich. S11 Ep14

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great British Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Attleborough to Skegness: Michael Portillo begins the last leg of his rail journey through 1930s Britain in Norfolk at the headquarters of an international horse welfare organisation. S11 Ep15

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great British Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Oxford to Abingdon: Michael Portillo sets out on another railway adventure as he explores Britain between the world wars, beginning a tour of the Home Counties and beyond in Oxford. S12 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Lotus Esprit/MGA: A series of head-turning supercharged cars head to the Mathewson's auction room. Plus, going under Derek's hammer - a Ford Escort XR3 and a beautiful MGA. S5 Ep7

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Saab 96L/AC Aceca: Derek heads out to pick up a pair of beautiful Swedish models - a Saab 96L and a Volvo P1800ES. Plus, a rare British AC Aceca comes up for sale. S5 Ep8

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Occupied Territories: The sabotaging efforts of Peugeot in Nazi-occupied France, where the bosses and workers cooperated with the Resistance to hinder the Nazis' use of military vehicles. S1 Ep6

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Tough Old Gut: The hugely respected chronology of WWII. Churchill described Italy as the 'soft underbelly of the crocodile', thinking the Allies could cut through it to reach Germany. S1 Ep13

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Beverley Minster 1: Fiona Bruce and her team of experts travel to Beverley Minster in East Yorkshire, where they value heirlooms including Victorian paintings and a medieval ring. S33 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Antiques Roadshow
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Beverley 2: The team pays a second visit to Beverley Minster, East Yorkshire, to examine objects including a pair of medical leech jars. S33 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: VW Golf Cabriolet: Derek and Paul are off to Leeds on a rare father and son road trip to pick up a VW Cabriolet and a Lotus Elite. S8 Ep1
